      "resolution_level": 4,
      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_mathematics_l3_vectors_in_space",
      "content": {
        "title": "Vector Components and Magnitude",
        "definition": "A vector v = ⟨a, b, c⟩ has magnitude |v| = √(a² + b² + c²) and direction specified by components.",
        "summary": "Component form enables algebraic vector operations and connects geometry to linear algebra."
      },
